    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "### Feature already in Vim?\n\nN/A\n\n### Feature description\n\n#16557 changed the behavior of floating window such that they now close when one navigates to a buffer other than two (the buffer that opened the float or the float itself).\r\n\r\nFor most use cases, this makes sense, but for cases where one is opening a nested group of tooltips, this means there's no longer a way to prevent the tooltips from closing.\r\n\r\nAn additional parameter should be added to `open_floating_preview` which should support keeping the old behavior.\r\n\r\n(First reported as Julian/lean.nvim#235)",
    "closed_at": null,
    "closed_by": null,
    "comment_data": [
        {
            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "I think we should move vim.lsp.util.open_floating_preview out to its own function, as it seems like the referenced upstream usecase is more because it's a convenient general purpose function, not for use in one of the pre-existing handlers. \r\n\r\nBasically @mfussenegger's comment [here](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/pull/17408#pullrequestreview-887351279) summarizes my opinion. Maybe you could state more exactly what you want from the API function and we can consider where to move it. Maybe `vim.ui.float`, or `vim.popup`.",
